---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Method — SecureProspective">
  <Nav />

  <main>
    {/* ───────────────────────── PAGE HERO ───────────────────────── */}
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container hero-inner">
        <div class="eyebrow">The Method</div>
        <h1 class="page-title">
          <span class="reveal-word">Diagnose.</span>
          <span class="reveal-word">Position.</span>
          <span class="reveal-word">Shape.</span>
          <span class="reveal-word">Transform.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">
          A four-movement discipline distilled from three careers. Not invented in a
          consulting deck. Derived from voltage, liability, and code.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ───────────────────────── STATION 01 — DIAGNOSE ───────────────────────── */}
    <section class="station station--white">
      <div class="container station-grid">
        <div class="station-text">
          <div class="station-label station-label--blue animate-in">01 / Diagnose</div>
          <h2 class="station-title animate-in">Find what's actually broken.</h2>
          <p class="station-body animate-in">
            Most consulting rushes to patch. The Diagnose movement does not. You meter the
            whole circuit before touching a single wire. You isolate the root failure — not
            the symptom. The wrong diagnosis is the most expensive mistake in any system,
            digital or physical. In fifteen years of electrical work, there was no margin
            for a wrong read. That discipline is now the first thing we do with every
            business.
          </p>
        </div>

        {/* CSS-drawn circuit / meter diagram with a highlighted break point */}
        <div class="circuit animate-in" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="circuit-frame">
            <div class="circuit-head">CIRCUIT // DIAGNOSTIC METER</div>
            <div class="circuit-track">
              <div class="circuit-line"></div>
              <span class="circuit-mark" style="left: 0%"></span>
              <span class="circuit-mark" style="left: 25%"></span>
              <span class="circuit-break" style="left: 50%">
                <span class="break-gap"></span>
                <span class="break-tag">FAULT</span>
              </span>
              <span class="circuit-mark" style="left: 75%"></span>
              <span class="circuit-mark" style="left: 100%"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="circuit-readout">
              <div><span>SRC</span> 120V</div>
              <div><span>ISO</span> 00.0V</div>
              <div><span>STATE</span> OPEN</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ───────────────────────── STATION 02 — POSITION ───────────────────────── */}
    <section class="station station--silver">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="station-label station-label--blue animate-in">02 / Position</div>
        <h2 class="station-title animate-in">Set the tool up for success.</h2>
        <p class="station-body animate-in">
          An AI tool placed wrong is worse than no AI tool. It creates confidence in the
          wrong output. Positioning means understanding the environment the tool enters —
          the people, the processes, the data flows, the places where a wrong output gets
          propagated as truth. From insurance case design: you never position a product
          without understanding the client's full picture first. That rigor now applies to
          every tool we place.
        </p>

        <aside class="annotation animate-in">
          <span class="annotation-mark">“</span>
          <p class="annotation-text">
            An AI tool placed wrong creates confidence in the wrong output.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ───────────────────────── STATION 03 — SHAPE ───────────────────────── */}
    <section class="station station--blue">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="station-label station-label--yellow animate-in">03 / Shape</div>
        <h2 class="station-title station-title--white animate-in">Structure output for ownership.</h2>
        <p class="station-body station-body--white animate-in">
          Output that no one understands is output no one owns. And output no one owns
          becomes a black box that the business depends on without being able to audit,
          correct, or improve. Shape means structuring every deliverable — every workflow,
          every document, every data pipeline — so the person receiving it can actually
          hold it. Not "AI generated this and we use it." Human-held, AI-assisted.
        </p>

        {/* Output schema grid */}
        <div class="schema animate-group" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="schema-box animate-item">FIELD_01</div>
          <div class="schema-box animate-item">FIELD_02</div>
          <div class="schema-box animate-item">FIELD_03</div>
          <div class="schema-box animate-item">FIELD_04</div>
          <div class="schema-box animate-item">FIELD_05</div>
          <div class="schema-box animate-item">FIELD_06</div>
          <div class="schema-box animate-item">FIELD_07</div>
          <div class="schema-box animate-item">FIELD_08</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ───────────────────────── STATION 04 — TRANSFORM ───────────────────────── */}
    <section class="station station--ink">
      <div class="container transform-inner">
        <div class="station-label station-label--yellow animate-in">04 / Transform</div>
        <h2 class="station-title station-title--white animate-in">AI-native. Prefix dropped.</h2>
        <p class="station-body station-body--white animate-in">
          AI-powered means you added a feature. AI-native means the architecture changed.
          The difference is the same as the difference between a building with a generator
          and a building that never needed the grid. Transform is when the business stops
          being the bottleneck — when the AI infrastructure it runs on is as native to the
          operation as the electrical wiring in the walls.
        </p>

        <p class="pull-quote animate-in">Not AI-powered. AI-native.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ───────────────────────── LOOP-CLOSER BANNER ───────────────────────── */}
    <section class="loop-banner">
      <div class="container loop-banner-inner animate-in">
        <p class="loop-banner-line">What's native today gets re-diagnosed tomorrow.</p>
        <p class="loop-banner-sub">
          The loop doesn't end — your business just stops being the bottleneck.
        </p>
        <a href="/the-work" class="btn btn--ink">See the work &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--silver-base);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--ink);
    padding: var(--space-8) 0;
  }
  .hero-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .page-title {
    font-size: var(--text-h1);
    line-height: 1.05;
    max-width: 900px;
  }
  .hero-sub {
    font-size: var(--text-body-lg);
    max-width: 640px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ── Stations shared ── */
  .station {
    padding: var(--space-7) 0;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--ink);
  }
  .station--white {
    background: var(--white);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--ink);
  }
  .station--silver {
    background: var(--silver-base);
  }
  .station--blue {
    background: var(--blue-brand);
    color: var(--ink-inverted);
  }
  .station--ink {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--ink-inverted);
  }

  .station-label {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .station-label--blue {
    color: var(--blue-brand);
  }
  .station-label--yellow {
    color: var(--yellow-accent);
  }

  .station-title {
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    max-width: 820px;
  }
  .station-title--white {
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .station-body {
    font-size: var(--text-body);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .station-body--white {
    color: var(--white);
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  /* ── Station 01 layout ── */
  .station-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    align-items: center;
  }
  .station-text {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .station-text .station-title {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ── Circuit diagram ── */
  .circuit {
    width: 100%;
  }
  .circuit-frame {
    border: 2px solid var(--ink);
    background: var(--silver-base);
    padding: var(--space-4);
  }
  .circuit-head {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 11px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }
  .circuit-track {
    position: relative;
    height: 56px;
    margin: 0 4px;
  }
  .circuit-line {
    position: absolute;
    top: 27px;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--ink);
  }
  .circuit-mark {
    position: absolute;
    top: 18px;
    width: 2px;
    height: 20px;
    background: var(--ink);
    transform: translateX(-1px);
  }
  .circuit-break {
    position: absolute;
    top: 18px;
    width: 14px;
    height: 20px;
    transform: translateX(-7px);
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .break-gap {
    width: 14px;
    height: 6px;
    background: var(--yellow-accent);
    margin-top: 7px;
  }
  .break-tag {
    position: absolute;
    top: -18px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--ink);
    background: var(--yellow-accent);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .circuit-readout {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink);
    padding-top: var(--space-3);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .circuit-readout span {
    opacity: 0.55;
    margin-right: 6px;
  }

  /* ── Station 02 annotation ── */
  .annotation {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold-identity);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .annotation-mark {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    color: var(--gold-identity);
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    line-height: 1;
    display: block;
  }
  .annotation-text {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-h3);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  /* ── Station 03 schema grid ── */
  .schema {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }
  .schema-box {
    border: 2px solid var(--white);
    color: var(--white);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    padding: var(--space-3);
    text-align: center;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  /* ── Station 04 pull quote ── */
  .transform-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .pull-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-h1);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--white);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    text-align: center;
    align-self: center;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  /* ── Loop-closer banner ── */
  .loop-banner {
    background: var(--yellow-accent);
    padding: var(--space-5) 0;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--ink);
  }
  .loop-banner-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .loop-banner-line {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-h3);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .loop-banner-sub {
    font-size: var(--text-body);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .station-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-5);
    }
    .schema {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .page-title {
      font-size: var(--text-h2);
    }
    .pull-quote {
      font-size: var(--text-h2);
    }
  }
</style>
